1 4. Implement a statewide public awareness campaign that includes information to reduce
2 stigma, encourage risk reduction activity, and emphasize the importance of early
3 detection and diagnosis.
4 SECTION 2. APPROPRIATION - DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES -
5 DEMENTIA RESPONSE PROGRAM - FULL-TIME EQUIVALENT POSITION. There is
6 appropriated out of any moneys in the general fund in the state treasury, not otherwise
7 appropriated, the sum of $250,000, or so much of the sum as may be necessary, to the
8 department of health and human services for the purpose of administering the dementia
9 response program, the behavioral risk factor surveillance models, and for a full-time equivalent
10 position to administer the program as the state dementia coordinator, for the biennium
11 beginning July 1, 2025, and ending June 30, 2027.
